abstract: Stephen Holden reviews performance by singer Dianne Reeves at Jazz at Lincoln Center’s Rose Hall.
lead_paragraph: Ms. Reeves paid tribute to the past powerhouses Billie Holiday and Sarah Vaughan, while pushing the borders of the genre on Friday.

headline.main: Review: Dianne Reeves Leads Journey of Jazz History at Rose Hall
headline.print_headline: Jazz at Its Heart, and Beyond
